    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) is a mechanically sound example of the final-year 996 evolution. Powered by the 3.6L M96 flat-six, it delivers linear power through a crisp 6-speed G96 manual transaxle. The IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the cooling system features a low-temp thermostat to mitigate thermal stress. Chassis dynamics remain sharp thanks to refreshed bushings and Bilstein B6 dampers. While the exterior shows minor road patina, the drivetrain is robust, with consistent compression across all cylinders and a leak-free undercarriage. A purist-spec driver\u2019s car ready for the canyons.",
